      • create

        public static <I> EntityRecordWithColumns<I> create(I id,
                                                    io.spine.server.entity.EntityRecord record)
        Creates the new instance of EntityRecordWithColumns using the pre-created entity record and the entity identifier.

        This method considers only the values of the lifecycle columns.

        Type Parameters:
        I - the type of the identifiers
        Parameters:
        id - the identifier of the entity
        record - the record to store; it is also used as a source for the lifecycle column values
        Returns:
        a new instance of EntityRecordWithColumns

      • of

        public static <I> EntityRecordWithColumns<I> of(io.spine.server.entity.EntityRecord record)
        Wraps a passed entity record into a EntityWithColumns with no storage fields.

        This is a shortcut for of(EntityRecord, Map) with an empty Map of storage fields.

        See Also:
        for the notes on usage

        Creates a new instance from the passed record and storage fields.
        API Note:
        This test-only method unpacks the identifier of the passed record and casts it to the type I. It is a responsibility of the caller to provide the record with the matching identifier.
